m introduces an in-principle\nindistinguishability between neighboring events, resulting in a network that is\ncoarse-grained, the thickness of the event being a function of the observer's\nclock.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2011 08:01:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 Jul 2012 14:21:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-26"}
